modules.description: This module implements flexible arrays using Braun trees, supporting efficient logarithmic-time operations for adding/removing elements at both ends (`cons`, `tail`, `snoc`, `liat`), indexed access and updates (`get`, `set`), and array construction (`make`, `init`, `of_array`, `of_list`). It provides functions for iteration (`iter`, `iteri`), folding (`fold`, `foldi`), and mapping (`map`, `mapi`) over elements, along with pretty-printing (`pp`). Concrete use cases include implementing queues or deques with efficient front and back operations, and working with dynamically sized arrays where elements need to be efficiently added or removed from either end.
